# Linux only. host-facts reports the host-fact registry (.chezmoidata/facts.yaml),
# and every probe behind it reads /sys, systemd, dpkg, or a Linux path — so off
# Linux the report is a page of `false` about a host it cannot describe. Deploying
# it there also renders a body shellcheck proves unreachable (SC2317), which is how
# this was caught: the CI job lints the RENDERED macOS output.
#
# import-wifi-1password provisions NetworkManager (Linux-only) Wi-Fi connections
# and bakes render-time-resolved op:// PSKs into its body (private_ 0700), so
# deploying it off Linux would resolve secrets into a copy that can never run —
# gate it out entirely.
{{- if ne .chezmoi.os "linux" }}
host-facts
import-wifi-1password
{{- end }}
